Rating: 0
Start with cut up frozen strawberries. Put all ingredients in a blender and make a slurry. Freeze in ice cream freezer. It takes about 5 minutes to freeze. For low fat, and dietetic ice cream, use splenda and non fat half and half

Rating: 3
Replace one cup of the heavy cream with light cream, or half-and-half. It will still be plenty rich, and you won't get a butterfat film on your spoon. It is worth noting that homemade ice cream has a different consistency than premium ice creams because home cooks don't use chemical stabilizers for mass production. If you do a taste test with this and a commerical strawberry, the one from the store will have a fake undertone to it. Even Haagen-Dazs.

