I've made two variations on this recipe and they were both fabulous. I didn't have heavy cream, so in one variation, I used whole milk, which was really good. Yes, as someone said, not as creamy as the premium ice creams, but I think that's overrated anyway. In the second variation, I used yogurt I had made from whole milk, without using lemon juice. Also fabulous. One day, I'll actually get some cream and try it as written. I used local strawberries that I bought during peak strawberry season and froze. Once they were thawed, I used a pastry cutter to mash/dice them, which worked very well. There were some little chunks, which gave it some chew, but mostly there was an intense strawberry flavor.

